<title type="html"><![CDATA[Measuring CPU and PPU Timing - Video Demonstration]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=16980&amp;p=212398#p212398"><![CDATA[
I'm working on a new project where I need a UI at the bottom of the screen, and in the process of learning how to make it work the way I wanted, <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=mXjgRf181V8" class="postlink">I decided to made a video about CPU/PPU cycle counting</a>.<br /><br />The video has examples of using the sprite 0 hit flag, troubleshooting with a debugger, optimizing code, and lots of info about HBlank and what happens during a scanline.<br /><br />I'm not sure if the particular use case in the video is actually that common, but I think it's still useful for getting an idea of how the CPU and PPU interact (the same idea can be adapted for mid-frame changing palettes/nametables/etc).<br />I think it's best watched as an example of how to do some of these things in general, and not so much as a tutorial.<br />(Although I'd really like to make some video tutorials in the future!)<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=8923">tragicmuffin</a> â€” Fri Jan 26, 2018 5:19 pm</p><hr />
